    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sheet metal seams having a bottom plate with a turned edge that is inserted inside the side plate; the seam may be secured by welding, soldering, or riveting at the overlapping joint. For bottom seams having the bottom plate with a turned edge that overlaps the side plate rather than being inserted inside it, use "lap bottom seams."</Note_Text>
